  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ 425°F/ Gas 7</p><p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Cover the <strong>dried ancho chilli<span class=\"text-danger\">[es]</span></strong> in <strong>boiled water </strong>and set aside to soak</p><p>Tear the <strong>portobellos</strong> and <strong>oyster mushroom mix</strong> into small pieces</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1594130461266-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1594130461266-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1594130461266-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1594130461266-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1594130461266-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>torn mushrooms </strong>to a <strong>non-stick baking paper</strong>-lined baking tray with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Put the tray in the oven for an initial 10-15 min or until the mushrooms have started to brown</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1594130476495-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1594130476495-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1594130476495-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1594130476495-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1594130476495-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> basmati rice </strong>and 250ml<span class=\"text-danger\"> [500ml] </span><strong>cold water </strong>to a pot with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and a lid and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 10-12 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once cooked, remove from the heat and keep covered until serving</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1594130515724-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1594130515724-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1594130515724-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1594130515724-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1594130515724-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Whilst the rice is cooking, carefully remove the <strong>ancho chilli<span class=\"text-danger\">[es]</span></strong> from the water and chop as finely as you can</p><p>Combine the <strong>chopped ancho chilli</strong> with the<strong> smoked paprika</strong>, <strong>half</strong> the <strong>tamari soy sauce</strong> (save the rest for later!), 1 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar </strong>and 1 tbsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tbsp] </span><strong>olive oil </strong>– this is your <strong>ancho chilli sauce</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1594130522591-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1594130522591-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1594130522591-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1594130522591-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1594130522591-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the mushrooms are starting to brown, remove them from the oven</p><p>Add the <strong>ancho chilli sauce</strong> and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Return the mushrooms to the oven for 10 min further or until golden and caramelised – these are your<strong> pulled ancho mushrooms</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
